(9, 'ab6d4663a9e79affe76ae01544841aef', 'Analisis de suelo', '<p><strong>ANALYSIS OF SOIL</strong></p>\n<p>Through over 50 years of international experience, network A &amp; L Laboratories in the United States and Canada has integrated various \\"packages\\" of special functional analysis for soils.</p>\n<p>They will announce the terms and parameters that appear in the reports of soil. Based on these measurements (26 parameters) suggestions and recommendations aimed at balanced fertilization Producer states.</p>\n<p>ISAOSA among its objectives to renew and expand its stock of traditional fertilizers and the use of new and modern fertilizer granules art supplies, and high quality soluble fertilizers, promotes the use of these inputs with the support of excellent soil analysis quality.</p>\n<p>ISAOSA early 2010, established an agreement with A &amp; L Canada Laboratories for provision of soil testing and plant analysis.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;"><strong>PLANS BALANCED FERTILIZATION.</strong></p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;">As an added value without extra cost to the producer, the Technical Area ISAOSA customer provides balanced fertilization plan annexed to the report of each soil analysis. This is a guide to the farmer about the type of source, rate, form and timing of the most suitable for your soil type and crop fertilizer; all with the aim of obtaining greater economic benefit to the rational use of fertilizers to achieve the given performance target.</p>\n<p><strong>PURPOSE OF SOIL AND PLANT ANALYSIS</strong></p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;">Soil testing in combination with analysis of the plant is an excellent way to develop magnificent balanced fertilization program for optimum production.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>STEPS IN THE ANALYSIS OF SOIL AND PLANT</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Representative Sampling</li>\n<li>Analytical Methods (Correlated and Calibrated)</li>\n<li>High Quality and Proper Interpretation of Results</li>\n<li>Balanced Fertilization Recommendation</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>GENERAL INFORMATION A &amp; L</strong></p>\n<p>A &amp; L Laboratories of Canada was founded in 1985. Located in London, Ontario and is one of the largest Agricultural and Environmental Laboratories in Canada. These laboratories are highly specialized in the analysis of soil, plant tissue, fertilizer and water. Corporation are affiliated with A &amp; L Laboratories covering an eight Analytical Laboratories, located regionally throughout the US. For over 25 years, A &amp; L Canada has been offering effective and reliable analytical services. It has a large staff of professionals in the fields of chemistry, agronomy and environmental science, always very willing to discuss individual requirements and technical guidelines be great. The Agricultural and authorized specialists can also provide comprehensive advice on mineral nutrition to crops and agriculture assistance programs through the techniques of GPS (Global Positioning Satellite Sampling). The Division of Environmental Studies covers all types of analysis in inorganic chemistry, organic chemistry, general chemistry and Pesticides.</p>\n<p>The permanent quality control is designed to always get the most accurate results, which includes the implementation of recognized methodologies that provide step by step procedures that ensure the integrity of all data generated through the use of statistical control techniques.</p>\n<p>A &amp; L Canada Laboratories highly accredited and certified by various international organizations including CAEL and OMAF.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">INSTRUCTIONS FOR TAKING, SHIPPING, RECEIVING AND PAYMENT SERVICE ANALYSIS OF SOIL SAMPLES</span></strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br /> - Take the soil sample as representative as possible, as follows: For each homogeneous piece of land (not more than 5 hectares), take 1 composite sample consisting of several sub-samples with hole or shovel blade straight. With random hole about 10-15 perforations 20 to 25 cm deep, then placing these sub-samples directly into the bag special role of A &amp; L Canada Labs.. When using shovel, make 4-5 holes randomly in a \\"V\\" at 25-30 cm depth; each hole to take a slice of soil from the surface to the bottom of the hole and go placing these portions of soil in a plastic container; either remove them by hand and take a handful of the jumble of about 200-300 grams which is placed in the respective exchange (see appendix).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;"><strong>Accompany displays the following information:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoTitle\\&quot;"><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">SOIL SAMPLE</span></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">COMPANY / UNDERTAKING: ..............................................................................</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">FARMER / RANCH: ...........................................................................</span></strong></p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;"><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">Domicilio: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;"><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">Plot / Plot: ........................... ..</span></strong></p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;"><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">Sample&nbsp; &nbsp;No. (ID): &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.................................</span></strong></p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;"><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">Cultivation: ........................... Variety: Growth Stage ........................ ............</span></strong></p>\n<p class="\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;"><strong><span lang="\\&quot;ES\\&quot;">Part of plant sampled: ...............................................................................</span></strong></p>\n<p